Here we see the comprehensive results for each model namely tinyllama,phi,gemma 2b
We measure their response to categories like logic ,coding,summarization,general knowledge and edge cases
We see their latency seconds, cpu percentage, ram percentage, response length and their response
The conclusion is that tinyllama is not functioning for a consumer hardware of limited ram while gemma 2b  takes peak usage of the ram, phi takes longer time to respond to edge cases and hasgenerally more latency than the other two models
From this we can say for a consumer hardware that does not use a gpu  gemma 2b is best

